  "text": "Though infectious diseases are threats to survival generally, their differential impact on infants and pregnant women makes them especially powerful selective agents. During pregnancy, the maternal immune system is suppressed so that the mother does not launch an adaptive immune response to the fetus's foreign cellular antigens [CITATION_1] .",
